feat(ui): enterprise login gate, staggered risk cards, mobile globe, luxe shadows

Enterprise flow
- Header "Enterprise" CTA now always routes to /enterprise/login
- Login page pre-fills believable random credentials every mount
- Successful login sends the user straight to /enterprise/risk-assessment
  (the dashboard remains one click away from the CTA grid there)

/risk/results cards
- Wrap the 3D preview, risk breakdown, building info, and insurance
  cards in <Reveal> so they animate in one-by-one (staggered index)
- Below-fold cards use whileInView so scrolling the report triggers
  each card's blur/translate entrance

Performance
- HSSBuildingPreview: IntersectionObserver gates frameloop between
  "always" and "demand" (no GPU work when offscreen), DPR capped to
  [1, 1.5], antialias only on desktop, shadows disabled, dynamic
  import so no three.js ships during SSR — fixes the /risk/results
  freezing on mid-range laptops

Home page / mobile
- Globe parks clearly below the Demo button on phones (translate Y
  45%, width capped at 280px) so it never overlaps the CTA stack
- On Demo the globe slides up + zooms into the card centre in one
  eased transform — reads as "slide up, then continue flying"

Luxury depth shadows
- New q-shadow-lux / q-shadow-soft / q-shadow-accent utilities with
  three-layer ambient + key-light + inset-highlight shadows
- Applied to the hero card, enterprise KPI & CTA cards, and the
  /risk/results info+insurance sections for a consistent premium feel

Verified: lints clean, tsc --noEmit clean, next build green (16 routes)
